1 facility or clinic or a public health department.
2 (4) "Place of religious worship" includes, but is not limited to, a
3 church, chapel, meetinghouse, synagogue, temple, mosque or any other
4 building that is regularly used and clearly identifiable as a place for
5 religious worship.
6 (5) "School" means:
7 (A) Any preschool, elementary school or secondary school
8 maintained and operated by a school district;
9 (B) any nonpublic organization that regularly offers preschool
10 educational or other programs or education satisfying the compulsory
11 school attendance laws of this state at the elementary or secondary level,
12 whether or not accredited by the state board of education;
13 (C) the site of any trade, technical or vocational training offered by a
14 school, whether or not located on school property; or
15 (D) the site of any school-sponsored function, event or activity,
16 whether or not located on school property.
17 Sec. 2. This act shall take effect and be in force from and after its
18 publication in the statute book.

